    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-20T18:01:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-20T18:01:00-05:00" n="14"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d14">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/2675: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_WW1" type="from"
                            >Wilson</persName> to King <persName corresp="#p_VE1" type="to">Victor
                            Emanuel</persName> of Italy</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-20T18:01:00-05:00"
                            >November 20, 1918—6:01 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your Majesty’s message of congratulation has given the deepest pleasure. I think
                    that it is a cause for particular pride on the part of the people of the United
                    States that they should have been able at the right time to assist in the great
                    struggle in which Italy has so distinguished herself, and I am sure that I speak
                    their heart in thanking Your Majesty with sincerest warmth for your message, and
                    in sending in return the heartfelt salutations of our own people.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
